Transcription.Text: Two samples of precipitated lead chromate (lead-210, bismuth-210) were counted and dissolved in nitric acid in silica basins. The bismuth was recovered from the eluate as the phosphate. Results did not differ from those obtained by the more convenient method of heating the disslved chromates in 2 N hydrochloric acid for fifteen minutes.
